    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The illusion of or erroneous perception of perspective; usually characterized by a subtly distorted depiction of three-dimensional objects, spatial relationships, and color, and by the perversion of the linear perspectival system.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>La ilusión o percepción errónea de perspectiva; usualmente caracterizada por una representación sutilmente distorsionada de objetos tri dimensionales, relaciones espaciales y color, y por la deformación del sistema de perspectivas lineal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>De illusie of foutieve waarneming van perspectief, gewoonlijk gekenmerkt door een subtiel verstoorde weergave van driedimensionale objecten, ruimtelijke verhoudingen en kleur, en door de verstoring van het lineaire perspectiefsysteem.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>假象或錯覺中的透視。常見特徵為將三維立體空間的物件、空間關係、色彩等加以微妙扭曲，以及非正規的線性透視系統等等。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
